Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
delete_relative_floorplan(25.10)              delete_relative_floorplan(25.10)

Name
       delete_relative_floorplan  - Removes the relative floorplan information
       from the database

Syntax
        delete_relative_floorplan

       [-help]

       {<obj_name_list >| -all}

       Removes the  relative  floorplan  information  from  the  database.  It
       deletes  all  relative  floorplan constraints, all relative constraints
       for the specified object(s), or  removes  the  last  executed  relative
       floorplan action from the database. Use this command after running cre-
       ate_relative_floorplan.

       Notes:

              * The  arrows showing relative constraints for the specified ob-
                jects are removed from the floorplan display.

              * The delete_relative_floorplan command accepts an array of  ob-
                jects.

Parameters
       -all   Delete all relative floorplan constraints.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each delete_relative_floorplan parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man delete_relative_floorplan

       <obj_name_list>
              Deletes all relative constraints for the specified object(s).

              Note: If you do not specify <obj_name_list>,  this  command  re-
              moves the last executed relative floorplan action from the data-
              base.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The  following  command  deletes obj1, obj2, and obj3 from the
                database:

                delete_relative_floorplan {obj1 obj2 obj3}

Related Information
              * create_relative_floorplan

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

